Unless the List entry states otherwise, it includes both the structure itself and any object or structure fixed to it (whether inside or outside) as well as any object or structure within the curtilage of the building.

ST 84 SW
10/98CORSLEY                    
WHITBOURNE SPRINGS (south side)
Nos 20 and 20AGV                                        
II
Pair of semi-detached cottages.  Mid C17,  Painted coursed rubble stone, tiled, pair of diagonally-set brick stacks in axial position. Two storey, five window north front. Planked doors to left and right, three single-light and two three-light recessed chamfered mullioned casements between.  First floor has four two-light mullioned casements and one wooden casement. Left return has C20 casements. Rear has pair of C20 wings, C20 steel casements. Interior said to have chamfered beams.Listing NGR: ST8338244433

DILTON MARSH              -
ST 85 SW
3/100                                    Tennis Corner Farmhouse
                                         with granary and stable
                                         II
Farmhouse.  Late C17.  Rubble stone, concrete tiled roof, brick
stacks.  Through passage to rear of stack.  Two-storey, 4-window
south front.  C20 porch to right of centre with 6-panelled inner
door with flat stone hood on brackets, 4-light cyma-mullioned
casement with hoodmould to right, two 4-light mullioned casements
with hoodmoulds to left.  First floor has three 3-light and one 2-
light mullioned casements, traces of former eyebrow dormers and
raised eaves.  Attached to left is 2-storey granary and stable with
entrance to first floor up wooden external stairs to rear;  planked
doors.  Rear of main range has lean-to porch with planked door to
left, 3-light casement and planked door to right, first floor has
four 3-light casements.  Interior not accessible at time of survey
(June 1986).
Listing NGR: ST8283950851
